<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Mercier</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-12-16"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 16, 1862.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Referring to my note of the 10th instant,
                            relative to the imprisonment of the Messrs. Lemore, alleged French
                            subjects, residing at New Orleans, I now have the honor to inform you
                            that, by a letter of the 12th instant from the War <pb facs="0143" n="821" xml:id="pg_821"/> Department, I learn that General Butler
                            has been instructed to remit the punishment of the ball and chain and
                            hard labor, to which they had been subjected.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, a renewed assurance of my very high consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Mergier</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>